{"title_page": "Leon Lyon", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name           = Leon Lyon\n| birth_name     = \n| fullname       = \n| nationality    = \n| residence      = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1918|8|3|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Payette, Idaho]], United States\n| death_date     = {{death date and age|2003|1|17|1918|8|3|df=yes}}\n| death_place    = [[San Juan, Puerto Rico|San Juan]], Puerto Rico\n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| website        = \n| country        = \n| sport          = [[Shooting sport|Sports shooting]]\n| event          = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = yes\n}}\n\n'''Leon Lyon''' (3 August 1918 &ndash; 17 January 2003) was a Puerto Rican [[Shooting sport|sports shooter]]. He competed at the [[1960 Summer Olympics]] and the [[1964 Summer Olympics]] in the Men's Rapid-Fire Pistol, 25 metres event.<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ly/leon-lyon-1.html |title=Leon Lyon |accessdate=24 June 2015 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lyon, Leon}}\n[[Category:1918 births]]\n[[Category:2003 deaths]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican male sport shooters]]\n[[Category:Olympic shooters of Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:Shooters at the 1960 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Shooters at the 1964 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:People from Payette, Idaho]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Idaho]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games medalists in shooting]]\n\n\n{{PuertoRico-sportshooting-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name           = Leon Lyon\n| birth_name     = \n| fullname       = \n| nationality    = \n| residence      = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1918|8|3|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Payette, Idaho]], United States\n| death_date     = {{death date and age|2003|1|17|1918|8|3|df=yes}}\n| death_place    = [[San Juan, Puerto Rico|San Juan]], Puerto Rico\