{"title_page": "Launi Meili", "text_new": "{{short description|American sport shooter}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name             = Launi Meili\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| fullname         = Launi Kay Meili\n| birth_date       = {{birth-date and age|June 4, 1963}}\n| birth_place      = [[Spokane, Washington]], U.S.\n| headercolor      = lightsteelblue\n| show-medals      = yes\n| medaltemplates   = \n{{MedalSport | Women's [[shooting (sport)|shooting]] }}\n{{MedalCountry | the {{USA}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Shooting at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]] }}\n{{MedalGold | {{nowrap|[[1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Barcelona]]}} | {{nowrap|[[Shooting at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 50 metre rifle three positions|50 m rifle 3 positions]]}} }}\n}}\n\n'''Launi Kay Meili''' (born June 4, 1963 in [[Spokane, Washington]])<ref>{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/me/launi-meili-1.html |title=Launi Meili |accessdate=May 29, 2015}}</ref> is an [[United States|American]] [[Shooting sports|sports]] [[shooting|shooter]] and Olympic champion from [[Cheney, Washington]]. She won a gold medal at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]].<ref name=db-ol>{{cite web|url=http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=23&sp=SHO |title=1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Barcelona, Spain \u2013 Shooting |website=databaseOlympics.com |accessdate=February 17, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080823075028/http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=23&sp=SHO |archivedate=August 23, 2008 }}</ref>\n\nFollowing her Olympic career, she coached the all-woman University of Nebraska rifle team to the co-ed NCAA National Championship. In 2008, she was appointed rifle coach at the [[United States Air Force Academy]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n! colspan=3 | Olympic results\n|-\n! Event\n! 1988\n! 1992\n|-\n| align=left | [[50 metre rifle three positions]]\n| style=\"background: #ccffcc\" | [[Shooting at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 50 metre rifle three positions|7th]]<br />582+94.5\n| style=\"background: #ccffcc\" | {{Gold1}} [[Shooting at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 50 metre rifle three positions|Gold]]<br />587+97.3\n|-\n| align=left | [[10 metre air rifle]]\n| style=\"background: #ccffcc\" | [[Shooting at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 10 metre air rifle|6th]]<br />395+98.3\n| [[Shooting at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 10 metre air rifle|11th]]<br />391\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Olympic Champions Shooting STR3X20}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Meili, Launi}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American female sport shooters]]\n[[Category:United States Distinguished Marksman]]\n[[Category:ISSF rifle shooters]]\n[[Category:Nebraska Cornhuskers rifle coaches]]\n[[Category:Shooters at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Shooters at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic shooters of the United States]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for the United States in shooting]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in shooting]]\n[[Category:Air Force Falcons rifle coaches]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Spokane, Washington]]\n[[Category:People from Cheney, Washington]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games medalists in shooting]]\n\n\n{{US-sportshooting-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American sport shooter}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name             = Launi Meili\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| fullname         = Launi Kay Meili\n| birth_date       = {{birth-date and age|June 4, 1963}}\n| birth_place      = [[Spokane, Washington]], U.S.\n| headercolor      = lightsteelblue\n| show-medals      = yes\n| medaltemplates   = \n{{MedalSport | Women's [[shooting (sport)|shooting]] }}\n{{MedalCountry | the {{USA}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Shooting at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]